Module kopper.tetris
Package kopper.tetris.core

Class Coord

  • java.lang.Object
    • kopper.tetris.core.Coord
  • public class Coord
extends Object
    A class to represent the x,y components of a Cartesian coordinate pair. The needs fulfilled by this class could have easily been fulfilled by Point, however, implementing my own version, was easier to make certain methods and operations specific to Tetris available.
    Author:
    KopperKnight

      • add

        public Coord add​(Coord c)
        Adds this coordinates to the specified coordinate and returns a newly instantiated resultant. This object is internally unaffected by the arguments or the result. In fact, supplying arguments representing a zero vector results in a newly instantiated clone of this coordinate object as a result.
        Parameters:
        c - The coordinate to add.
        Returns:
        The resultant coordinate that is the sum of this coordinate and the argument coordinate.

      • add

        public Coord add​(int x,
                 int y)
        Adds this coordinates's x and y values to the specified coordinate's x and y values and returns a newly instantiated coordinate with x and y values being the sum result. This object is internally unaffected by the arguments or the result. In fact, supplying arguments representing a zero vector results in a newly instantiated clone of this coordinate object as a result.
        Parameters:
        x - The x value to add to this coordinates x value.
        y - The y value to add to this coordinate y value.
        Returns:
        The resultant coordinate that is the sum of this coordinate and the argument coordinate.
